= SDL_SetTextureColorMod =
Use this function to set an additional color value used in render copy operations.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_SetTextureColorMod(SDL_TextureID textureID,
                           Uint8         r,
                           Uint8         g,
                           Uint8         b)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''textureID'''
|the texture to update
|-
|'''r'''
|the red source color value multiplied into copy operations
|-
|'''g'''
|the green source color value multiplied into copy operations
|-
|'''b'''
|the blue source color value multiplied into copy operations
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or -1 if the texture is not valid or color modulation is not supported; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

